I found the issue! The `addtodo` method is missing error handling around the `fetch_projects_with_subprojects` call. Unlike the main `todo` method which has an `eval` block and error handling, the `addtodo` method calls it directly without any error handling. If the project fetching fails, `$projects` would be undefined, causing the project selection dropdown to be blank.

🔄 **PROPOSED CHANGE TO:** `/home/shanta/PycharmProjects/comserv2/Comserv/lib/Comserv/Controller/Todo.pm`
📝 **CHANGE TYPE:** Modification
📋 **DESCRIPTION:** Add error handling around project fetching in addtodo method to prevent blank project selection dropdown

❌ **CURRENT CODE:**
```perl
    # Fetch project data from the Project Controller
    my $project_controller = $c->controller('Project');
    my $projects = $project_controller->fetch_projects_with_subprojects($c);
```

✅ **NEW CODE:**
```perl
    # Fetch project data from the Project Controller
    my $projects = [];
    eval {
        my $project_controller = $c->controller('Project');
        if ($project_controller) {
            $projects = $project_controller->fetch_projects_with_subprojects($c) || [];
        }
    };

    if ($@) {
        $self->logging->log_with_details($c, 'error', __FILE__, __LINE__, 'addtodo',
            "Error fetching projects: $@");
    }
```

💡 **REASON:** The addtodo method lacks error handling around project fetching, which can cause the project selection dropdown to be blank if the fetch fails. This adds the same error handling pattern used in the main todo method.

⚠️ **APPROVAL REQUIRED:** Please confirm with "approved" or "yes"
🔄 **REVERT:** Changes can be undone if needed

